# Always Push to GitHub

When you finish implementing requested code changes in this repo:

1. Commit the relevant changes with a concise message (focus on why).
2. Push to `origin/main` (or the user's active feature branch if one is in use).
3. Tell the user the commit hash and that the push succeeded.

Do not skip push because the user did not repeat "GitHub에 올려" in that turn.

## Git safety

- Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials).
- Do not force-push to `main`.
- Do not amend unless the user explicitly asked or a hook auto-modified files on your commit.
- If push to `main` is blocked, retry with user approval rather than leaving commits local only.

## When not to push

- Question-only or review-only tasks with no file edits.
- User explicitly says not to commit/push yet.
- Changes are intentionally local experiments the user asked to keep uncommitted.
